events.name: Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Marqise Lee caught a 75-yard touchdown pass on the first play from scrimmage and returned a kickoff 100 yards for a score, and No. 1 Southern California rolled to a 49-10 victory over Hawaii on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lee, Barkley power No. 1 USC in rout

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron threw two touchdown passes and Alabama's retooled defense showed it could still dominate as the second-ranked Crimson Tide pounded No. 8 Michigan 41-14 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bama dominates in win vs. Michigan

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Kenny Hilliard rushed for 141 yards and two touchdowns, and No. 3 LSU opened its season with a 41-14 victory over North Texas on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hilliard powers No. 3 LSU past North Texas

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at UTEP Miners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw two touchdown passes and Damien Williams ran 65 yards for another score in the fourth quarter, helping No. 4 Oklahoma slog out a 24-7 win over Texas-El Paso on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oklahoma pulls away late from UTEP

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota made his first start in a real game on Saturday night, passing for 200 yards and three touchdowns in No. 5 Oregon's 57-34 season-opening victory over Arkansas State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota shines as Oregon rips Arkansas St.

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Freshman tailback Todd Gurley ran for three touchdowns, Aaron Murray threw three scoring passes and No. 6 Georgia overcame a sloppy first half to beat Buffalo 45-23 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: UGA recovers after sloppy half

events.name: Murray State Racers at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Lonnie Pryor, James Wilder Jr., and Debrale Smiley combined for seven rushing touchdowns Saturday to lead No. 7 Florida State to a 69-3 win over Murray State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pryor runs for 3 TDs as FSU blisters Murray St.

events.name: Jacksonville State Gamecocks at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson set the school record for yards passing in a season opener, finishing 19 of 27 passing for 367 yards and three touchdowns to lead Arkansas to a 49-24 win over Jacksonville State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson starts season strong as Arkansas rolls

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for 323 yards and four touchdowns to lead No. 11 West Virginia to a 69-34 win over Marshall on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: WVU rolls Marshall for highest scoring opener

events.name: Northern Iowa Panthers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Montee Ball rushed for 120 yards and a touchdown, and No. 12 Wisconsin needed a big defensive play to survive a fourth-quarter scare from Northern Iowa in a 26-21 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin survives scare

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Andre Ellington rushed for 231 yards, DeAndre Hopkins set a school record with 13 receptions and No. 14 Clemson opened the season with 26-19 victory over Auburn on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ellington, Clemson edge past Auburn

events.name: Wyoming Cowboys at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Joe Bergeron and Malcolm Brown both rushed for more than 100 yards and combined for three touchdowns, leading No. 15 Texas to a 37-17 win over Wyoming on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bergeron and Brown push Texas by Wyoming

events.name: Southern Mississippi Golden Eagles at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez threw for a career-high 354 yards and matched his high with five touchdown passes to lead No. 17 Nebraska to a 49-20 victory over Southern Mississippi on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Martinez throws 5 TDs as Nebraska rolls

events.name: Miami (OH) RedHawks at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller rushed for 161 yards, a record for an Ohio State quarterback, and threw for two scores to pace the Buckeyes in Urban Meyer's debut as coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miller, OSU roll in Meyer's debut

events.name: Savannah State Tigers at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Jeremy Smith and Desmond Roland ran for three touchdowns apiece, Wes Lunt completed all 11 of his passes as the new starting quarterback as No. 19 Oklahoma State outmatched Savannah State 84-0 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Savannah St. crushed 84-0, but pockets $385K

events.name: Missouri State Bears at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Collin Klein threw for 169 yards and two touchdowns, John Hubert ran 95 yards for a fourth-quarter score and No. 22 Kansas State pulled away late to beat Missouri State 51-9 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas State pulls away late vs. Missouri State

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Mike Gillislee had a career-high 148 yards rushing and two touchdowns, helping No. 23 Florida beat Bowling Green 27-14 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gillislee's rushing career-high lifts Gators

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Notre Dame 50, Navy 10
headlines.shortLinkText: ND routs Navy in Ireland

events.name: Troy Trojans at UAB Blazers

headlines.description: Troy 39, UAB 29
headlines.shortLinkText: Troy 39, UAB 29

events.name: Appalachian State Mountaineers at East Carolina Pirates

headlines.description: East Carolina 35, Appalachian St. 13
headlines.shortLinkText: East Carolina 35, Appalachian St. 13

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Backup quarterback Trevor Siemian hit Demetrius Fields for a 9-yard touchdown pass with 44 seconds left and Northwestern held on to beat Syracuse 42-41 Saturday in the teams' season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: N'western erases Syracuse rally with late TD

events.name: Ohio Bobcats at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: The new era at Penn State is off to a disappointing start.
headlines.shortLinkText: PSU upset by Ohio in opener

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: With quarterback Nathan Scheelhaase injured, Ashante Williams returned an interception 60 yards for a fourth-quarter touchdown to help Illinois and new coach Tim Beckman hang on for a 24-7 win over Western Michigan.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois wins opener despite Scheelhaase injury

events.name: Elon Phoenix at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Gio Bernard had three first-half touchdowns and North Carolina had its biggest scoring day in 17 years to beat Elon 62-0 on Saturday in the debut of new coach Larry Fedora.
headlines.shortLinkText: N. Carolina embarrasses Elon in shutout victory

Idaho State Bengals at Air Force Falcons

headlines.description: Air Force 49, Idaho St. 21
headlines.shortLinkText: Air Force 49, Idaho St. 21

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Stefphon Jefferson ran for 141 yards and scored his third touchdown with 36 seconds remaining as Nevada spoiled the reopening of Memorial Stadium by beating California 31-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nevada spoils California's stadium reopening

events.name: William & Mary Tribe at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Justus Pickett ran for a 6-yard touchdown with 9:52 left in the fourth quarter, and Brad Craddock added the tie-breaking extra point to give Maryland a 7-6 victory over William & Mary in the season opener for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TD in fourth lets Maryland edge William & Mary

events.name: Richmond Spiders at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Michael Rocco threw for 311 yards and a touchdown and Virginia beat Richmond 43-19 in the season opener for both teams Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rocco tops 300 yards as Virginia rips Richmond

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Steele Jantz threw for 281 yards and two touchdowns and ran for another score as Iowa State beat Tulsa 38-23 Saturday to win its ninth opener in 10 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa St. trumps Tulsa to stay hot in openers

events.name: Miami Hurricanes at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Freshman Duke Johnson broke two long touchdown runs, rushing for 135 yards to lead Miami to a 41-32 victory over Boston College on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson, Miami rolls past Boston College

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Damon Bullock ran for 150 yards and scored on a late 23-yard touchdown run to lead Iowa to an 18-17 victory over Northern Illinois in the season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bullock rescues Iowa from Northern Illinois

events.name: Eastern Kentucky Colonels at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Robert Marve passed for a career-high 295 yards and matched a career best with three touchdowns to help Purdue defeat Eastern Kentucky 48-6 on Saturday in both teams' season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marve steps in, leads Purdue in opening rout

events.name: Colorado State Rams at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Jim McElwain became the first Colorado State coach to win his debut in 42 years Saturday when the Rams rallied past their arch rival for a 22-17 win over the Colorado Buffaloes.
headlines.shortLinkText: McElwain wins coaching debut for Colorado St.

headlines.description: New Mexico 66, Southern U. 21
headlines.shortLinkText: New Mexico 66, Southern U. 21

headlines.description: James Madison 55, St. Francis (Pa.) 7

headlines.description: Georgia Southern 58, Jacksonville 0
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia Southern 58, Jacksonville 0

headlines.shortLinkText: Coastal Carolina 29, NC A&amp,T 13

events.name: Liberty Flames at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Redshirt freshman Deandre Martin scored the go-ahead touchdown in the fourth quarter on a 2-yard run as Wake Forest came from behind to defeat Liberty 20-17 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake Forest rallies to stymie Liberty's upset bid

events.name: Youngstown State Penguins at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Kurt Hess passed for 154 yards and two touchdowns as Youngstown State of the Football Championship Subdivision spoiled Paul Chryst's debut as Pittsburgh's coach in a 31-17 upset on Saturday night in the season opener for both schools.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chryst era at Pitt begins with loss to FCS team

events.name: Chattanooga Mocs at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: B.J. Daniels threw for 265 yards and three touchdowns, helping South Florida open the season with a 34-13 victory over Chattanooga on Saturday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Daniels tosses 3 TDs to power USF to victory

headlines.description: W. Kentucky 49, Austin Peay 10
headlines.shortLinkText: W. Kentucky 49, Austin Peay 10

events.name: Southeastern Louisiana Lions at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Marcus Murphy scored on punt returns of 72 and 70 yards and Zaviar Gooden and Michael Sam fueled a lightning-fast start with early defensive touchdowns in Missouri's 62-10 season-opening rout of Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Missouri starts fast in trouncing of SE Louisiana

events.name: Central Arkansas Bears at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Bo Wallace threw for 264 yards and two touchdowns in his Football Bowl Subdivision debut as Mississippi rallied to beat Central Arkansas 49-27 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wallace rallies Ole Miss past Central Arkansas

events.name: Florida Intl Golden Panthers at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Sean Renfree threw for 290 yards and two touchdowns, and Duke scored 30 points in the second quarter of its 46-26 rout of Florida International on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duke uses 30-point 2nd quarter to put away FIU

headlines.description: UT-Martin 20, Memphis 17
headlines.shortLinkText: UT-Martin 20, Memphis 17

Jackson State Tigers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Tyler Russell completed 15 of 23 passes for 175 yards and two touchdowns to lead Mississippi State to a season-opening 56-9 win over Jackson State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mississippi St. trounces Jackson St. in opener

events.name: South Dakota State Jackrabbits at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Tony Pierson rushed for two touchdowns, Dayne Crist connected with former Notre Dame teammate Mike Ragone on a short touchdown pass, and Kansas launched the Charlie Weis era Saturday night with a 31-17 victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kansas launches Charlie Weis era with victory

events.name: Northwestern State Demons at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Eric Stephens ran for two touchdowns to lead Texas Tech over Northwestern State 44-6 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephens runs for two scores in Texas Tech win

events.name: Indiana State Sycamores at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Tre Roberson threw for a career-high 280 yards and one touchdown, ran for another and led Indiana past in-state rival Indiana State 24-17 Saturday night in the season opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana tops Indiana St. to end 9-game skid

headlines.description: Texas St. 30, Houston 13
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas St. 30, Houston 13

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Tulane Green Wave

headlines.description: Jawan Jamison ran for a 46-yard touchdown, Brandon Jones returned an interception for a score to lead Rutgers to a 24-12 victory over Tulane on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamison's 46-yard TD run paces Rutgers' win

headlines.description: Fresno St. 37, Weber St. 10
headlines.shortLinkText: Fresno St. 37, Weber St. 10

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Matt Scott scrambled and threw a 10-yard touchdown pass to Terrence Miller in overtime to give Arizona a 24-17 victory over Toledo Saturday night in Rich Rodriguez's coaching debut in the desert.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona wins in overtime in Rodriguez's debut

events.name: San Diego State Aztecs at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Washington raced to an early lead then held on for a 21-12 win over San Diego State on Saturday night.
